title: Megan Rapinoe will play her final soccer game tonight before retirement
description: U.S. soccer legend Megan Rapinoe will play her final professional game against Gotham FC on Saturday night at San Diego’s Snapdragon Stadium.

title: House Republicans unveil their plan to avert a government shutdown next week
description: House Republicans unveiled their stopgap bill to avoid a government shutdown ahead of next weekend's deadline.

title: Trump backs requests for TV coverage of his federal criminal trial
description: Donald Trump has filed a legal motion backing media requests for live television coverage of his federal trial on charges he conspired to overturn the results of the 2020 presidential election.

title: American Vets: Benefits, Race & Inequality
description: For years, Black veterans have been denied disability benefits at higher rates than their white counterparts. NBC News and NBC stations around the country investigated the disparities in this special report. And the reporting is getting results.

title: Palestinian journalists in Israel say they face intimidation and harassment
description: As Israeli authorities crack down on broadcasts and reports they deem a threat to national security, several Palestinian journalists say they were harassed by police.

title: 6 dead in Houston crash after driver allegedly runs red light
description: Six people are dead and a seventh had life-threatening injuries after a speeding driver allegedly ran a red light and caused a crash with a sport-utility vehicle in Houston early Saturday, police said.

title: Man in custody in slaying of Detroit Jewish community leader Samantha Woll released without charges
description: A xx-year-old (geography, where's he from?) man ("man" unless we know something more about his job relationship to Woll) was charged on Friday with the slaying of prominent Jewish community leader Samantha Woll, police said.

title: Pilot accused of trying to stop engines mid-flight after taking magic mushrooms questioned 'Am I dead? Is this hell?'
description: The off-duty Alaska Airlines pilot accused of trying to shut down the engines of an airborne plane last month after taking magic mushrooms thought he was dreaming and had questioned if he was in hell, he said in an interview published Saturday.

title: Mother of slain Nashville college freshman Jillian Ludwig says 'a piece of my heart' was taken
description: The mother of a Nashville college student who was killed by a stray bullet said "there's a piece of my heart that was taken" as her father questioned why a repeat criminal allegedly responsible for the crime was released back on the street.

title: Why buying a house is still financially beneficial even with sky-high prices and interest rates
description: It’s becoming harder to enter the U.S. housing market, but for those who have managed to get in, the benefits have often been huge.

title: Wegovy shows promise for heart disease
description: A new clinical trial found that weight loss drug Wegovy shows promise for lowering the risk of heart attack and stroke among people with heart disease and obesity.

title: Muslim students feel abandoned by U. of Texas after Israelis disrupt Palestinian event
description: The pro-Palestinian students believe that the incident has laid bare a double standard that exists in how the university responds to acts of hate.

title: After debate clash, Ron DeSantis and Nikki Haley turn back to the battle for Iowa
description: For one night this week, Ron DeSantis and Nikki Haley battled face-to-face in Miami. Now, they’re trying to bring momentum from the debate week back to Iowa.

title: Feminist consumers in China push back against the ‘pink tax’
description: Feminist consumers in China are pushing back against the “pink tax,” or higher prices on products that are aimed at them.

title: RNC threatens to ban candidates from debates if they attend Iowa group’s forum
description: Several candidates have been invited by the Family Leader Foundation to participate in an event that will include a “moderated, friendly and open discussion.”

title: Several children with cancer and serious blood disorders evacuated from Gaza
description: More than a dozen children with cancer or other serious blood disorders have been safely evacuated from Gaza after weeks of difficult negotiations involving the U.S., Egypt, Israel and Hamas — but more than 30 remain in the war-torn territory, three doctors involved in the effort tell NBC News.

title: Florida teacher fired for using gender-neutral honorific ‘Mx.’
description: A Florida teacher filed a complaint against their former employer after being fired for using the gender-neutral honorific “Mx.”

title: Louisiana legislators have until Jan. 15 to enact new congressional map, court says
description: A lower court last year ruled that the current political boundaries of Louisiana's congressional map dilute the power of the state’s Black voters.

title: Nightly News Full Broadcast (November 10th)
description: Strikes near hospitals in Gaza as Israel-Hamas war intensifies; FBI seizes electronic devices from NYC Mayor Eric Adams; Georgia man arrested over threat to kill Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene; and more on tonight’s broadcast.

title: Group of Jews and Arabs come together to spread peace in Israel
description: A group of Jews and Arabs are working together to protect each other and spread peace across Jaffa in Israel. The group, which has around three thousand members, spreads posters and flyers with a helpline for those reporting violence.

title: MDMA could help veterans with PTSD, researchers say
description: Many veterans are impacted by post-traumatic stress disorder. Now researchers say MDMA, a psychedelic drug, could serve as part of a promising new treatment for it. NBC News’ Harry Smith has more details.
